raw_data.title: Research Associate
raw_data.description: Experience in the assessment of research needs, establishment of methodologies, development of research tools and procedures; review and approval of deliverable reports and studies. Assists Senior Research Associates in peforming research that will help inform the development of managerial or organizational options and the development of criteria for assessing these options.  Analyzes datasets and secondary research materials. Designs and implements scientifically rigorous research to obtain new data.  Applies expertise in applying appropriate quantitative analysis (e.g., statistical analyses using procedures such as multilevel modeling, classical regression techniques) or qualitative analysis. Expertise in conducting quantitative and qualitative research.  Identifies questionable or erroneous data, reviews and determines statistical accuracy of studies compiles or reviews conclusions and research summaries. For IT projects, applies these skills in assisting senior Research Assocaites in developing and implementing methods for defining requirements for IT systems, assessing relationships between data elements, and defining meaningful output reports for stakeholders at varying levels within an organization. For talent development and training projects, helps implement research to support the development of training materials and course syllabi, and curricula.  Applies knowledge of relevant legislative, regulatory, and policy issues. Excellent computer skills, especially in the use of word processing programs, spreadsheet programs, statistical software, and possesses strong Internet research skills. Knowledge of Performance Based Services Contracting desired.

raw_data.title: Senior Subject Matter Expert I
raw_data.description: Serves as senior expert in a functional, technical, scientific, IT, human resources, academic, regulatory, operations, government mission, or other specialty area.  Recognized as national expert in field or discipline with demonstrated and documented academic and practical, in-depth knowledge of specific field of expertise.  May serve as a task lead and supervise others to complete project tasks and deliverables. Possesses specialized expertise in technical and organizational areas.  For management consulting projects, may advise the project team or client organization in specific areas of expertise and applies domain-specific expertise to help identify options for achieving mission success, assess optimal organizational structures, and recommend optimal managerial and organizational changes. Participates as needed across project phases.  Assists clients in conducting studies, evaluations, and implementation of projects and systems. Applies principles, methods, and knowledge towards the project approach, deliverables, reports, representations, or quality control. For IT related projects, applies domain expertise to help define IT system requirements, define database structures, and assess accuracy and efficacy of standard and ad hoc reporting modules.   For training and talent development projects, applies expertise to help identify training requirements within his or her domain of expertise, and helps develop appropriate training strategies and content.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 1 year of relevant experience is equivalent to a High School Degree; a High School Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to an Associate Degree;  an Associate Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Bachelor’s Degree; a Bachelor’s Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Master’s Degree.

labor_categories.years_experience: 1 year of relevant experience is equivalent to a High School Degree; a High School Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to an Associate Degree;  an Associate Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Bachelor’s Degree; a Bachelor’s Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Master’s Degree.

raw_data.title: Senior Research Associate II
raw_data.description: Experience in the assessment of complex or advanced research needs, establishment of methodologies, development of research tools and procedures; review and approval of deliverable reports and studies.   Provides leadership in selected methodological areas, and takes lead role in complex research and evaluation projects. Identifies questionable or erroneous data, reviews and determines statistical accuracy of studies compiles or reviews conclusions and research summaries. Applies deep knowledge of relevant legislative, regulatory, and policy issues. Plays a strategic role in developing and expanding new studies in the subject matter areas of interest to clients. Supervises and directs research staff. For IT projects, applies these skills in developing and implementing methods for defining requirements for IT systems, assessing relationships between data elements, and defining meaningful output reports for stakeholders at varying levels within an organization.  For management and strategic consulting projects, applies these skills in performing research that will help inform the development of managerial or organizational options and the development of criteria for assessing these options.  For talent development and training projects helps design and implement research to support the development of training materials course syllabi, and curricula. Excellent computer skills, especially in the use of word processing programs, spreadsheet programs, statistical software, and possesses strong Internet research skills. Knowledge of Performance Based Services Contracting desired.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 1 year of relevant experience is equivalent to a High School Degree; a High School Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to an Associate Degree;  an Associate Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Bachelor’s Degree; a Bachelor’s Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Master’s Degree.

labor_categories.years_experience: 1 year of relevant experience is equivalent to a High School Degree; a High School Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to an Associate Degree;  an Associate Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Bachelor’s Degree; a Bachelor’s Degree plus 2 years of relevant experience is equivalent to a Master’s Degree.
